</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/01 5:18:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: For me</span><hr size=1> Are you sure those griffawns are killable at level 12. I found myself dying all the way at level 12. Only when I reach level 16 did I manage to kill those thing. <p>Mejision - level 23 Human Mage<BR>
Yishen - level 10 Human Cleric<BR>
Woofwoof - level 14 Bard shaman<BR>
Zlazher - level 16 Troll SK<BR>
Monnkey - level 16 Human Monk<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uknorotpumaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knorot Pumaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/01 3:59:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: how to avoid dying at level 12 :)</span><hr size=1> Well EK is a good place to hunt and it is less crowded than Oasis, now that is a good thing if you want to solo.  I know as mages we tend to solo, because we can, but if you are looking for groups you will have to probably stick to hunting in Oasis or wandering stuff in WC.<br>
<br>
Also take a look at the where to hunt forums listed here.<br>
<br>
 <p><img src="http://www.attcanada.ca/~reeder/temp1/sig2a.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugranthisrz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Granthis RZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(4/9/01 5:13:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: how to avoid dying at level 12 :)</span><hr size=1> Lavastorm is also a fun but challenging place to do 12-16.  Break out your ward summoned/ cancel magic and go to town on the fire elementals (be sure to con them), fire drakes, and rock dervishes.  When you feel like something a bit more challenging at 15 or so, try a fire imp or lava crawler.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uamik2002.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amik2002</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(6/1/01 2:58:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   EK or bust</span><hr size=1> I love East Karanas to hunt at 12th level or so if I'm soloing (I will be with the Mage..). I've done this before with a Druid and it's also a pretty good place to kite with a couple of zones to go to. You can bind yourself on the bridge heading into NK so that way if you get into any trouble you can gate, let your pet be eaten and zone to NK with minimal running. There are some dangers in this zone so beware... These include:<br>
<br>
Griffawns, Griffons and the variations of course<br>
Undead Reavers<br>
Evil Eye<br>
Droon, Broon and the other cyclops.<br>
<br>
Generally this isn't a problem. After binding on the bridge to NK what I always do is run back to the bottom of the ramp to HHP. Once I'm there and facing the ramp I swing a left and start running straight. You'll come to King Xorb's entrance or whatever it is called and see a lot of Gorge Hounds and other things around. There is a little village back there with guards that attack some of the roaming monsters. Great place to hunt with some pull back if you get into trouble. I believe the guards will only kill the spiders and chasm crawlers as I have yet to see them take out a Silvermist Wolf, Lion, Lioness, Lion Matriarch, etc... so they must like the animals. Obviously, they are't taking out the Evil Eye if it roams over... just move out of the Eye's way it doesn't have a huge agro radius. You could probably do this zone to 17 or 18 with relative ease. <br>
<br>
If you REALLY feel brave and don't mind running through a crowd of hording spiders (Weblurkers) and other nasties then you can take the boat from Freeport to ButcherBlock and from Butcherblock to Fironia Via. Once in Fironia Via run to Swamp of No Hope. In Swamp of No Hope just follow the left-hand &quot;wall&quot;. Eventually Cabilis will come into sight, avoid it, just sneak around the edges of it where the cement and buildings are and you should be fine if their isn't a crusader out patrolling (generally not). Once there go back to the left again and you'll see a opening on the left. Run through that and keep following it back and you'll eventually zone into Field of Bone. Field of Bone is the Iksar newbie area and is good from levels 1-20 (realistically 23 but my Monk started greening on everything at 20th with only a minimal amount of blues left). Just bind yourself at the top of Kurn's Tower and if you get into trouble you can either run to the top of the ramp or you can just let your pet get eaten and zone into Kurn's. Kurn's is also a great dungeon to get some experience using the pet in a dungeon that has tricky pathing.<br>
<br>
Amik Asim<br>
Iksar Monk of the 21st Shackle<br>
<br>
Conjured<br>
8th level High-Elf Mage<br>
